<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="810" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d810">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14325.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 1, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Benjamin Hill is in command of city during the absence of Obregon
                            in Vera Cruz. Zapatistas continue to occupy the farthest southern
                            suburbs; they still control and have cut the main city water supply. The
                            Constitutionalists are operating the Mexican Railway.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>